We all know the first 3 seconds of a video decide whether someone watches or scrolls.

And for the longest time, I was wasting those 3 seconds.

😬 Pretty intro shots.
😬 Slow pans.
😬 Me just smiling at the camera.

Then I tried this 👇

(First Save this video so you don’t lose it! Okay, now here you go-)

🎯 I started using pattern interrupts.

A pattern interrupt is anything unexpected that grabs attention — here’s what I used:

• A bold statement (controversial truth)
• Zoom-in or sudden motion
• Hook + jump cut into action
• ASMR sound effects

Just this 3-second fix? My retention doubled. (Which means better reach + better results for clients.)

Don’t sleep on your intro. It’s where trust begins.

Let’s be honest: we’ve all spent hours editing a reel only to have it flop.

So I tried something different.
I posted 30 days of raw, low-effort, ugly-first-draft content. No transitions. No fancy edits. Just value + vibes.

Results? 🤯

✅ More engagement than polished reels
✅ Better reach (algorithm loves authentic!)
✅ A few videos even got reposted by brands

Here’s why it works:

First, save this reel so you don’t lose you. Okay here you go-

	1.	Authenticity wins. People relate more to “real” over curated.
	2.	Less editing = more consistency. You actually post more.
	3.	You test faster. Which formats are converting? You find out quicker.

💡 Takeaway: Done > Perfect. Ugly-first drafts have power.

✨ I even turned one of those drafts into a paid ad for a skincare brand.
